Package: leechcraft-lmp
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 leechcraft-core (= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: ffmpeg, leechcraft-lastfmscrobble,
 leechcraft-provider-removabledevicemgr,
 leechcraft-provider-globalshortcuts,
 leechcraft-provider-radiostreams
Provides: leechcraft-provider-mediaplayer
Description: Music Player for LeechCraft
 This package contains the LMP (LeechCraft Music Player), a collection-oriented
 music player based on Phonon. Currently it features:
  * Collection-oriented music player with playback statistics.
  * Collection synchronization with portable media players, with transcoding.
  * Support for scrobbling played tracks to services like Last.FM.
  * Automatic fetching of album art if it's not present.
  * Support for requesting a bunch of information from services like Last.FM,
    including: artist biography, similar artists, personalized recommendations,
    recent releases by the artists in user's library, events nearby, hyped
    tracks and artists.
  * Fetching artists' discographies from MusicBrainz.
  * Previewing artsits, tracks and albums from VKontakte.
  * Support for fetching lyrics.
  * Support for radio streams (of course, including Last.FM radio).
  * Play queue with different play modes like sequential, shuffle, repeating
    track/album/whole playlist.
  * MPRIS support.
  * Undo/redo for play queue.
  * Dynamic playlists like "50 Random Tracks".
  * Static playlists.
  * Support for M3U8, PLS and XSPF playlist formats.
  * Fast threaded collection scanner.
 .
 Some features in the above list rely on other plugins like LastFMScrobble.
 .
 Such sub-plugins are also available in this package:
  * dumbsync (for uploading files to USB flash-like media players)
  * mp3tunes (for synchronization with the corresponding service)
  * graffiti (for editing audo tags)
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
 .
 LeechCraft allows one to browse the web, read RSS/Atom feeds, download
 files via BitTorrent, HTTP, FTP and Direct Connect, automatically stream,
 download or play podcasts and other media files and much more.

Package: leechcraft-monocle
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 leechcraft-core (= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: leechcraft-provider-sessionmanager
Description: Document viewer for LeechCraft
 This package contains Monocle, the modular document reader for LeechCraft.
 Currently it has the following backend modules:
  * fxb -- FictionBook file format (*.fb2)
  * pdf -- PDF file format (*.pdf) (libpoppler is used)
  * seen -- DjVu file format (*.djvu) (libdjvulibre is used)
  * postrus -- PostScript file format (*.ps) (libspectre is used)
 .
 Monocle supports links and tables of contents, two-page spreads, copying
 selection as image or text, fullscreen presentation mode and has a bunch
 of other features.
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
 .
