Package: leechcraft-poshuku
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
 leechcraft-core (= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: leechcraft-provider-http,
 leechcraft-provider-bittorrent,
 leechcraft-provider-feedreader,
 leechcraft-provider-search,
 leechcraft-provider-mediaplayer,
 leechcraft-provider-sessionmanager
Provides: leechcraft-provider-webbrowser
Description: Web browser for LeechCraft
 This package contains a full-featured web browser for LeechCraft based
 on WebKit. Poshuku is fully extensible with plugins. Currently it features:
  * support for all major web-standards
  * integration with other plugins
  * autodiscovery
  * tagging bookmarks
  * support for SQLite or PostgreSQL storage
 .
 Such sub-plugins are available in this package:
  * cleanweb (Ad filter for Web browser)
  This is a plugin for the Poshuku web browser that filters out ads according to
  predefined rules. It is compatible with Firefox's AdBlock rules list files.
  It also supports disabling Flash and allowing it to load only after you click
  on the corresponding button.
  * fatape (GreaseMonkey support layer)
  The Poshuku FatApe plugin adds support for GreaseMonkey scripts to the Poshuku
  browser. FatApe also supports basic scripts management, allowing to install or
  remove them easily.
  * filescheme (file://-schemes support)
  This is a plugin for the Poshuku web browser that allows it to handle file://
  schemes.
  * fua (Fake user agent plugin)
  This is a plugin for the Poshuku web browser that allows it to set fake user
  agents for different domains or even URLs based on regexps.
  * keywords (Support of url keywords)
  * onlinebookmarks (Support for syncing bookmarks with online services)
  This is a plugin for the Poshuku web browser that allows it to synchronize
  local bookmarks with online social bookmarking systems like Read It Later.
  * pintab (Support of pinned tab)
  * pogooglue (Support for searching selected text in Google)
  This is a plugin for the Poshuku web browser that replaces default flash-based
  video players on some sites with any suitable LeechCraft's media player thus
  avoiding the need for Flash. First you should install package:
  leechcraft-provider-mediaplayer
 .
 LeechCraft is a free modular "Internet client" application.
 .
 LeechCraft allows one to browse the web, read RSS/Atom feeds, download
 files via BitTorrent, HTTP, FTP and Direct Connect, automatically stream,
 download or play podcasts and other media files and much more.

